deck: Writer for X-Files 30 Days of Night #1
description:
Adam Thomas Jones is a multy-tasking dude, but before all, known as the guitarist and co-founder of the progressive metal band TOOL.   

He has an artistic background and draws TOOL album covers and posters, and also makes the design and direct the video clips.   In 2007 he received the Grammy Award for " Best Recording Packag e" as Art Director for his work on 10.000 Days (TOOL last album).    
He started playing music as a bass player with Tom Morello from Rage Against The Machine before creating TOOL.
He also designed the make up and set design of famous movies such as: Jurassic Park, Terminator 2, Ghostbusters 2, A nightmare on Elm Street 4 and 5.
name: Adam Jones

deck: French artist. Known for La Survivante (The Survivor) and Les naufragés du temps (Lost in Time).
description: Paul Gillon was born in 1926, and was a prominent French comic artist and author. Co-Creator (along with Jean-Claude Forest) of the science fiction cosmic opera series, Naufragés du Temps (Lost in Time) and the erotic comic series, La Survivante (The Survivor). Other titles worked on are Jérémie, Lynx Blanc, Wango, Les Léviathans and more. In 1982, Gillon won the Grand Prix de le ville d'Angoulême, for his achievements in the evolution of comics, an award also given to such talents as Will Eisner, Jean "Moebius" Giraud, Robert Crumb, and more recently, Katushiro Otomo, Art Spiegelman and Bill Watterson. Gillon passed away in 2011.
name: Paul Gillon
